'''César Rodolfo Blackman Camarena''' (born 2 April 1998) is a Panamanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|right-back]] for [[Slovak First Football League]] club [[ŠK Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Blackman made his [[Slovak Super Liga|Fortuna Liga]] debut for [[FC DAC 1904 Dunajská Streda|Dunajská Streda]] against [[MFK Ružomberok|Ružomberok]] on 10 March 2018.<ref>[https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2018/03/10/slovakia/super-liga/dac-1904-dunajska-streda/mfk-ruomberok/2749856/ DAC VS. RUŽOMBEROK 3 - 0] 10.03.2018, soccerway.com</ref>

==International career==
He made his debut for the [[Panama national football team]] on 23 March 2019 in a friendly against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], as an 85th-minute substitute for [[Michael Amir Murillo]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/commentary?gameId=537099|title=Brazil v Panama game report|date=23 March 2019}}</ref>

